OL,3,GSouth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a chilly but sunny start,
OL,6,Fcloud will build from the north with
OL,7,Fpatchy rain possible by midday.
OL,8,FTurning drier through the afternoon
OL,9,Fwith sunny spells developing, with
OL,10,Fsome parts perhaps staying dry
OL,11,Fthroughout.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FDry overnight with variable
OL,14,Famounts of cloud and lengthy clear
OL,15,Fspells developing. A risk of a rural
OL,16,Fgrass frost in the east. Turning
OL,17,Fcloudier from the north towards dawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
